a-Cola%2C%20and%20Ferrero%20and%20that%20UPFs%20accounted%20for%20about%2030%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20his%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUPFs%2C%20which%20are%20made%20using%20ingredients%20and%20processes%20you%20wouldn't%20find%20in%20a%20regular%20kitchen%2C%20are%20a%20key%20feature%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwestern-style-diet-impairs-brain-leads-to-overeating-study-finds-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWestern%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202024%20research%20paper%20by%20Northeastern%20University's%20Network%20Science%20Institute%2C%20which%20hasn't%20been%20peer-reviewed%2C%20found%20they%20made%20up%2073%25%20of%20the%20US%20food%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20said%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-research-explains-why-cant-stop-eating-chips-ice-cream-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehyper-palatable%3C%2Fa%3E%20foods%20contain%20the%20perfect%20fat-to-carbohydrate%20ratio%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20near-impossible%20for%20us%20to%20stop%20eating%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20foods%20that%20are%20so%20desired%20by%20our%20system%20that%20they%20actually%20slow%20down%20our%20satiety%20mechanisms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Research%20published%20in%20Nature%20Food%20last%20year%20found%20that%20the%20more%20hyper-palatable%20foods%20there%20were%20in%20a%20meal%2C%20the%20more%20calories%20participants%20tended%20to%20eat%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20started%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20UPFs%20around%202020%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarbs-eating-leftovers-reheated-weight-loss-nutritionist-advice-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Chris%20van%20Tulleken%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%20bestselling%20book%20%26quot%3BUltra%20Processed%20People%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20shines%20a%20light%20on%20the%20harms%20of%20industrial%20food%20processing%2C%20asked%20him%20on%20his%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20wanted%20to%20find%20out%20from%20me%20what%20are%20all%20the%20sensory%20tricks%20and%20the%20hacks%20of%20our%20senses%20that%20go%20on%20in%20food%20manufacture%20and%20food%20formatting%20that%20get%20us%20to%20consume%2C%20desire%2C%20crave%20these%20foods%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20made%20him%20more%20conscious%20of%20the%20health%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20a%20study%20published%20in%20February%20in%20The%20BMJ%20linked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-health-problems-study-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUPFs%20to%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%2032%20health%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20cardiovascular%20disease%20%E2%80%94%20and%20reflect%20on%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20came%20to%20see%20how%20in%20a%20slightly%20unknowing%20way%2C%20I%20was%20maybe%20aiding%20and%20abetting%20these%20moves%20by%20the%20food%20industry%20and%20began%20to%20think%2C%20no%2C%20I%20simply%20can't%20in%20good%20conscience%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20companies%20hire%20sensory%20scientists%20and%20chemists%20to%20help%20make%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-linked-early-death-study-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUPFs%3C%2Fa%3E%20irresistible%2C%20but%20they%20tend%20not%20to%20eat%20the%20products%20they%20help%20create%2C%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20know%20what%20the%20design%2C%20the%20formatting%2C%20the%20industrial%20processing%20is%20about.%20So%20they%20don't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20eat%20them%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20no%20longer%20works%20with%20UPF%20companies%20(although%20he%20said%20he%20never%20advised%20on%20how%20to%20make%20food%20that%20people%20can't%20stop%20eating).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20shared%20three%20things%20that%20helped%20him%20change%20his%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bebb77b7-bbc7-4a62-bd81-153dd6256ca1%5C%22%3ETake%20a%20break%20from%20UPFs%20first%20(and%20you%20may%20not%20want%20to%20go%20back)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20Smith%20learned%20about%20the%20health%20risks%20of%20UPFs%2C%20the%20less%20he%20wanted%20to%20eat%20them%2C%20so%20he%20decided%20to%20cut%20them%20out%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20realized%20he%20didn't%20like%20that%20they%20had%20a%20physiological%20effect%20on%20him%2C%20and%20over%20time%2C%20he%20started%20to%20actively%20dislike%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20seem%20too%20intense%2C%20over-flavored%2C%20too%20shouty%20in%20some%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20noticed%20that%20he%20felt%20better%20for%20it.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20consciously%20cutting%20out%20ultra-processed%20food%20because%20of%20the%20bad%20things%20it%20might%20do%20for%20my%20health.%20And%20then%20found%20the%20effects%20were%20so%20desirable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20felt%20more%20energetic%2C%20full%20for%20longer%2C%20and%20able%20to%20stop%20eating%20when%20he%20felt%20full.%20He%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-processed-food-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20weight%20without%20trying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20this%20is%20because%20he%20was%20hooked%20on%20UPFs%20before%2C%20rather%20than%20actually%20enjoying%20them%2C%20and%20taking%20a%20break%20from%20them%20allowed%20him%20to%20see%20them%20for%20what%20they%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCutting%20out%20that%20craving%2C%20you%20find%20yourself%20resorting%20to%20quite%20natural%20intake%20regulation%20where%20you%20don't%20overeat%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20these%20are%20foods%20that%20we%20necessarily%20like%20more%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20but%20they're%20foods%20that%20we%20want%20and%20can't%20seem%20to%20stop%20wanting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20worked%20for%20Smith%2C%20going%20cold%20turkey%20isn't%20for%20everyone.%20As%20the%20registered%20dietitian%20Linia%20Patel%20previously%20told%20BI%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwant-to-cut-down-on-upfs-3-questions-to-ask-yourself-dietitian-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20back%20on%20UPFs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20creating%20any%20new%20habit%20involves%20changing%20our%20behavior%2C%20so%20it's%20helpful%20to%20unpack%20what%20works%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20hand%20holding%20a%20cheeseburger%20with%20fries%20and%20a%20drink%20on%20a%20tray%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662f7f72ec0c696569fe8edb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECutting%20back%20on%20UPFs%20can%20help%20us%20question%20whether%20we%20actually%20enjoy%20them%20or%20are%20just%20hooked.%20%3Cp%3EAleksandr%20Zubkov%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229edd2bda-18ea-44b9-b9b1-660087bffba2%5C%22%3ECheck%20food%20labels%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20said%20checking%20the%20nutrition%20labels%20on%20food%20items%20had%20helped%20him%20choose%20minimally%20processed%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he'd%20found%20that%20even%20some%20items%20you'd%20expect%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bperfectly%20OK%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20a%20tin%20of%20grocery-store%20kidney%20beans%2C%20could%20contain%20gelling%20agents%20or%20stabilizers.%20He%20gets%20around%20this%20by%20opting%20for%20organic%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20this%20highlights%20how%20eating%20a%20healthy%20diet%20can%20be%20dependent%20on%20a%20person's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-insecurity-harder-to-lose-weight-study-finds-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20environment%20and%20socioeconomic%20status%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218f78ef4-9eb2-4632-bd5c-3ef92894cddb%5C%22%3EFind%20genuinely%20tasty%20alternatives%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20professor%20of%20the%20senses%2C%20Smith%20is%20interested%20in%20the%20multisensory%20experience%20of%20eating.%20%26quot%3BHow%20things%20look%2C%20how%20they%20smell%2C%20the%20feel%20on%20the%20fingers%2C%20even%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20food%20when%20you're%20snapping%20something%20or%20when%20you're%20shaking%20something%20up.%20All%20of%20those%20things%20are%20part%20of%20the%20experience%20of%20tasting%20and%20eating%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20crucial%20to%20take%20this%20into%20account%20when%20shifting%20away%20from%20UPFs%20that%20have%20been%20manufactured%20to%20be%20delicious%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20going%20to%20persuade%20people%20to%20move%20away%20from%20ultra-processed%20food%20by%20telling%20them%20it's%20bad%20for%20them.%20It's%20got%20to%20be%20flavor%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20nutritious%2C%20vegetables%20can%20be%20quite%20boring%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20there%20are%20many%20ways%20to%20make%20them%20interesting%2C%20such%20as%20roasting%2C%20pickling%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-gut-health-dietitian-sneaks-fermented-foods-into-her-diet-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efermenting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20make%20them%20really%20tasty%20so%20that%20people%20realize%2C%20'I%20can%20actually%20make%20something%20reasonably%20cheap%20and%20reasonably%20well%20that%20I'm%20actually%20going%20to%20enjoy%20eating%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientist-lost-weight-without-trying-quit-ultra-processed-foods-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%