%20past%20six%20decades%20have%20been%20middle-aged%20men%20on%20short-duration%20missions%20of%20fewer%20than%2020%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20with%20private%2C%20commercial%20and%20multinational%20spaceflight%20providers%20and%20flyers%20entering%20the%20market%2C%20we%20are%20witnessing%20a%20new%20era%20of%20human%20spaceflight.%20Missions%20have%20ranged%20from%20minutes%2C%20hours%20and%20days%20to%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20humanity%20looks%20ahead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Freturning-to-the-moon-can-benefit-commercial-military-and-political-sectors-a-space-policy-expert-explains-209300%5C%22%3Ereturning%20to%20the%20Moon%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20coming%20decade%2C%20space%20exploration%20missions%20will%20be%20much%20longer%2C%20with%20many%20more%20space%20travelers%20and%20even%20space%20tourists.%20This%20also%20means%20that%20a%20wider%20diversity%20of%20people%20will%20experience%20the%20extreme%20environment%20of%20space%20%E2%80%93%20more%20women%20and%20people%20of%20different%20ethnicities%2C%20ages%20and%20health%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20people%20respond%20differently%20to%20the%20unique%20stressors%20and%20exposures%20of%20space%2C%20researchers%20in%20space%20health%2C%20like%20me%2C%20seek%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20human%20health%20effects%20of%20spaceflight.%20With%20such%20information%2C%20we%20can%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20help%20astronauts%20stay%20healthy%20both%20while%20they're%20in%20space%20and%20once%20they%20return%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aau8650%5C%22%3Ehistoric%20NASA%20Twins%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%202019%2C%20my%20colleagues%20and%20I%20published%20groundbreaking%20research%20on%20how%20one%20year%20on%20board%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20affects%20the%20human%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DnvFtqMoAAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3Eradiation%20cancer%20biologist%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Colorado%20State%20University's%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20and%20Radiological%20Health%20Sciences.%20I've%20spent%20the%20past%20few%20years%20continuing%20to%20build%20on%20that%20earlier%20research%20in%20a%20series%20of%20papers%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fimmersive%2Fd42859-024-00009-8%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Epublished%20across%20the%20portfolio%20of%20Nature%20journals%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20papers%20are%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fimmersive%2Fd42859-024-00009-8%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ESpace%20Omics%20and%20Medical%20Atlas%20package%20of%20manuscripts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20data%2C%20protocols%20and%20repositories%20that%20represent%20the%20largest%20collection%20ever%20assembled%20for%20aerospace%20medicine%20and%20space%20biology.%20Over%20100%20institutions%20from%2025%20countries%20contributed%20to%20the%20coordinated%20release%20of%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20spaceflight%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20NASA%20Twins%20Study%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aau8650%5C%22%3ETwins%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%20seized%20on%20a%20unique%20research%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20selected%20astronaut%20Scott%20Kelly%20for%20the%20agency's%20first%20one-year%20mission%2C%20during%20which%20he%20spent%20a%20year%20on%20board%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20from%202015%20into%202016.%20Over%20the%20same%20time%20period%2C%20his%20identical%20twin%20brother%2C%20Mark%20Kelly%2C%20a%20former%20astronaut%20and%20current%20U.S.%20senator%20representing%20Arizona%2C%20remained%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fdoes-a-year-in-space-make-you-older-or-younger-111812%5C%22%3EMy%20team%20and%20I%20examined%20blood%20samples%3C%2Fa%3E%20collected%20from%20the%20twin%20in%20space%20and%20his%20genetically%20matched%20twin%20back%20on%20Earth%20before%2C%20during%20and%20after%20spaceflight.%20We%20found%20that%20Scott's%20telomeres%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcells-become-zombies-when-the-ends-of-their-chromosomes-are-damaged-a-tactic-both-helpful-and-harmful-for-health-186445%5C%22%3Ethe%20protective%20caps%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20ends%20of%20chromosomes%2C%20much%20like%20the%20plastic%20tip%20that%20keeps%20a%20shoelace%20from%20fraying%20%E2%80%93%20lengthened%2C%20quite%20unexpectedly%2C%20during%20his%20year%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Scott%20returned%20to%20Earth%2C%20however%2C%20his%20telomeres%20quickly%20shortened.%20Over%20the%20following%20months%2C%20his%20telomeres%20recovered%20but%20were%20still%20shorter%20after%20his%20journey%20than%20they%20had%20been%20before%20he%20went%20to%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20get%20older%2C%20your%20telomeres%20shorten%20because%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20stress.%20The%20length%20of%20your%20telomeres%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41556-022-00842-x%5C%22%3Eserve%20as%20a%20biological%20indicator%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20your%20risk%20for%20developing%20age-related%20conditions%20such%20as%20dementia%2C%20cardiovascular%20disease%20and%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.celrep.2020.108435%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20separate%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20team%20studied%20a%20cohort%20of%2010%20astronauts%20on%20six-month%20missions%20on%20board%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20We%20also%20had%20a%20control%20group%20of%20age-%20and%20sex-matched%20participants%20who%20stayed%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20measured%20telomere%20length%20before%2C%20during%20and%20after%20spaceflight%20and%20again%20found%20that%20telomeres%20were%20longer%20during%20spaceflight%20and%20then%20shortened%20upon%20return%20to%20Earth.%20Overall%2C%20the%20astronauts%20had%20many%20more%20short%20telomeres%20after%20spaceflight%20than%20they%20had%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20other%20Twins%20Study%20investigators%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DvId_OTEAAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Mason%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.celrep.2020.108457%5C%22%3Econducted%20another%20telomere%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20this%20time%20with%20twin%20high-altitude%20mountain%20climbers%20%E2%80%93%20a%20somewhat%20similar%20extreme%20environment%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20while%20climbing%20Mount%20Everest%2C%20the%20climbers'%20telomeres%20were%20longer%2C%20and%20after%20they%20descended%2C%20their%20telomeres%20shortened.%20Their%20twins%20who%20remained%20at%20low%20altitude%20didn't%20experience%20the%20same%20changes%20in%20telomere%20length.%20These%20results%20indicate%20that%20it's%20not%20the%20space%20station's%20microgravity%20that%20led%20to%20the%20telomere%20length%20changes%20we%20observed%20in%20the%20astronauts%20%E2%80%93%20other%20culprits%2C%20such%20as%20increased%20radiation%20exposure%2C%20are%20more%20likely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivilians%20in%20space%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1093%2Fpcmedi%2Fpbae007%5C%22%3EIn%20our%20latest%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20studied%20telomeres%20from%20the%20crew%20on%20board%20SpaceX's%202021%20Inspiration4%20mission.%20This%20mission%20had%20the%20first%20all-civilian%20crew%2C%20whose%20ages%20spanned%20four%20decades.%20All%20of%20the%20crew%20members'%20telomeres%20lengthened%20during%20the%20mission%2C%20and%20three%20of%20the%20four%20astronauts%20also%20exhibited%20telomere%20shortening%20once%20they%20were%20back%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20particularly%20interesting%20about%20these%20findings%20is%20that%20the%20Inspiration4%20mission%20lasted%20only%20three%20days.%20So%2C%20not%20only%20do%20scientists%20now%20have%20consistent%20and%20reproducible%20data%20on%20telomeres'%20response%20to%20spaceflight%2C%20but%20we%20also%20know%20it%20happens%20quickly.%20These%20results%20suggest%20that%20even%20short%20trips%2C%20like%20a%20weekend%20getaway%20to%20space%2C%20will%20be%20associated%20with%20changes%20in%20telomere%20length.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20still%20don't%20totally%20understand%20the%20health%20impacts%20of%20such%20changes%20in%20telomere%20length.%20We'll%20need%20more%20research%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20both%20long%20and%20short%20telomeres%20might%20affect%20an%20astronaut's%20long-term%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETelomeric%20RNA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs42003-024-06014-x%5C%22%3EIn%20another%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20showed%20that%20the%20Inspiration4%20crew%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20Scott%20Kelly%20and%20the%20high-altitude%20mountain%20climbers%20%E2%80%93%20exhibited%20increased%20levels%20of%20telomeric%20RNA%2C%20termed%20TERRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelomeres%20consist%20of%20lots%20of%20repetitive%20DNA%20sequences.%20These%20are%20transcribed%20into%20TERRA%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20telomere%20structure%20and%20helps%20them%20do%20their%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20laboratory%20studies%2C%20these%20findings%20tell%20us%20that%20telomeres%20are%20being%20damaged%20during%20spaceflight.%20While%20there%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20we%20don't%20know%2C%20we%20do%20know%20that%20telomeres%20are%20especially%20sensitive%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fhealth%2Foxidative-stress%5C%22%3Eoxidative%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20the%20chronic%20oxidative%20damage%20that%20astronauts%20experience%20when%20exposed%20to%20space%20radiation%20around%20the%20clock%20likely%20contributes%20to%20the%20telomeric%20responses%20we%20observe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20wrote%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1007%2Fs10522-024-10098-7%5C%22%3Ereview%20article%20with%20a%20more%20futuristic%20perspective%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20how%20better%20understanding%20telomeres%20and%20aging%20might%20begin%20to%20inform%20the%20ability%20of%20humans%20to%20not%20only%20survive%20long-duration%20space%20travel%20but%20also%20to%20thrive%20and%20even%20colonize%20other%20planets.%20Doing%20so%20would%20require%20humans%20to%20reproduce%20in%20space%20and%20future%20generations%20to%20grow%20up%20in%20space.%20We%20don't%20know%20if%20that's%20even%20possible%20%E2%80%93%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlant%20telomeres%20in%20space%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20colleagues%20and%20I%20contributed%20other%20work%20to%20the%20Space%20Omics%20and%20Medical%20Atlas%20package%2C%20as%20well%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41467-023-41510-4%5C%22%3Ea%20paper%20published%20in%20Nature%20Communications%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20study%20team%2C%20led%20by%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20biologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DnHjDBNIAAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3EDorothy%20Shippen%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Ohio%20University%20biologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.com%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DyXhk2d4AAAAJ%26hl%3Den%5C%22%3ESarah%20Wyatt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20found%20that%2C%20unlike%20people%2C%20plants%20flown%20in%20space%20did%20not%20have%20longer%20telomeres%20during%20their%20time%20on%20board%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plants%20did%2C%20however%2C%20ramp%20up%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.gov%2Fpublications%2Fdictionaries%2Fcancer-terms%2Fdef%2Ftelomerase%5C%22%3Eproduction%20of%20telomerase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20enzyme%20that%20helps%20maintain%20telomere%20length.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20anyone%20who's%20seen%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt3659388%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Martian%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20knows%2C%20plants%20will%20play%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20long-term%20human%20survival%20in%20space.%20This%20finding%20suggests%20that%20plants%20are%20perhaps%20more%20naturally%20suited%20to%20withstand%20the%20stressors%20of%20space%20than%20humans.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F232967%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fsusan-bailey-689607%5C%22%3ESusan%20Bailey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Radiation%20Cancer%20Biology%20and%20Oncology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fcolorado-state-university-1267%5C%22%3EColorado%20State%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Feven-short-trips-to-space-can-change-an-astronauts-biology-a-new-set-of-studies-offers-the-most-comprehensive-look-at-spaceflight-health-since-nasas-twins-study-232967%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720433880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2F7l7ds8j8_astronaut-generic_625x300_25_July_