ry%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20a%20double%20mastectomy%20regardless%20of%20the%20results.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gila%20Pfeffer%20sitting%20outside%20on%20a%20white%20chair%20wearing%20a%20white%20shirt%20and%20holding%20sunglasses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66747d1c65f501a88180dbef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGila%20Pfeffer%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BNearly%20Departed%3A%20Adventures%20in%20Loss%2C%20Cancer%2C%20and%20Other%20Inconveniences.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Sarah%20Raanan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGila%20Pfeffer%20is%20a%20humor%20writer%20who%20splits%20her%20time%20between%20NYC%20and%20London.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20adapted%20excerpt%20from%20her%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BNearly%20Departed%3A%20Adventures%20in%20Loss%2C%20Cancer%2C%20and%20Other%20Inconveniences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20chronicles%20her%20journey%20as%20a%20cancer%20previvor%20and%20survivor%2C%20determined%20to%20reverse%20the%20cycle%20of%20death%20in%20her%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEleven%20years%20after%20my%20mother%20died%20in%201994%2C%20when%20I%20was%2031%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20a%20simple%20blood%20test%20could%20confirm%20whether%20I%20was%20a%20carrier%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrca2-mutation-genetic-test-proactive-health-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBRCA%20gene%20mutation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Named%20for%20the%20first%20two%20letters%20of%20%26quot%3Bbreast%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcancer%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20positive%20result%20would%20place%20my%20odds%20of%20developing%20breast%20cancer%20at%2087%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20added%20bonus%2C%20BRCA%20carriers%20have%20a%2066%25%20chance%20of%20being%20hit%20with%20ovarian%20cancer.%20Those%20sound%20pretty%20high%20until%20you%20consider%20my%20insanely%20strong%20family%20history%20of%20cancer%2C%20which%20cranked%20my%20risk%20up%20even%20further.%20A%20blood%20test%20would%20be%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20formality%2C%20a%20scientific%20breakthrough%20to%20tell%20me%20what%20I%20instinctively%20knew.%20I%20would%20100%25%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-daughter-and-i-have-brca1-gene-mutation-breast-cancer-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBRCA-positive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22705238e6-6935-4c84-b128-dd4747e20383%5C%22%3ETesting%20wasn't%20a%20common%20practice%20yet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%202005%2C%20and%20genetic%20testing%20was%20far%20from%20commonplace.%20The%20famous%20Human%20Genome%20Project%2C%20an%20international%20effort%20to%20generate%20the%20first%20complete%20sequence%20of%20the%20human%20genome%2C%20had%20only%20recently%20achieved%20its%20goal%20by%20producing%20a%20sequence%20that%20decoded%2092%25%20of%20human%20DNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20growing%20buzz%20around%20mainstream%20genetic%20testing%20and%20although%20we%20were%20still%20years%20away%20from%20at-home%20spit%20tests%20like%2023andMe%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FAncestry.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAncestry.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20development%20could%20tell%20me%20exactly%20what%20my%20body%20was%20up%20against.%20After%20a%20decade%20of%20playing%20defense%2C%20I'd%20finally%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20shift%20to%20offense.%20I%20could%20see%20a%20path%20to%20reversing%20my%20family's%20health%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPregnant%20with%20my%20third%20child%20and%20sick%20of%20everyone%20in%20my%20family%20dying%20too%20young%2C%20my%20self-preservationist%20instincts%20went%20into%20overdrive.%20I%20already%20thought%20about%20my%20own%20mortality%20way%20more%20than%20your%20average%2030-year-old%2C%20but%20my%20obsession%20didn't%20stop%20there.%20I%20had%20my%20younger%20sisters%20and%20baby%20daughter%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20too.%20Because%20my%20sisters%20were%20still%20children%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-mom-died-of-an-overdose-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20mother%20died%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20primary%20impact%20on%20them%20was%20that%20it%20rendered%20them%20motherless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20an%20adult%2C%20it%20was%20a%20wake-up%20call%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbreast-cancer-double-mastectomy-health-editor-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebreast%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20family%20matriarch%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20responsibility%20to%20take%20preventive%20measures%20not%20only%20for%20my%20own%20sake%2C%20but%20to%20set%20a%20good%20example%20for%20my%20siblings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222818a67d-62c8-47a3-88d1-cac08a7c4420%5C%22%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20my%20friend%20had%20a%20prophylactic%20double%20mastectomy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20I%20learned%20about%20genetic%20testing%2C%20my%20friend%20Stephanie%20told%20me%20she%20was%20scheduled%20to%20have%20a%20procedure%20called%20a%20prophylactic%20double%20mastectomy.%20That's%20a%20lot%20of%20syllables%20that%20amount%20to%20electively%20removing%20healthy%20breast%20tissue%20before%20cancer%20can%20take%20root.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20I'd%20ever%20heard%20of%20it%2C%20and%20my%20immediate%20reaction%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReconstruction%20is%20usually%20done%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20unless%20a%20woman%20chooses%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20flat.%26quot%3B%20Unlike%20the%20modified%20radical%20mastectomy%20my%20mother%20eventually%20underwent%2C%20the%20prophylactic%20version%20leaves%20the%20outer%20skin%20and%20sometimes%20the%20nipple%20and%20areola%20intact.%20It%20would%20be%20years%20before%20Angelina%20Jolie%20would%20make%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-had-a-preventative-double-mastectomy-age-25-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprophylactic%20double%20mastectomy%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20a%20household%20phrase%20by%20writing%20an%20opinion%20piece%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20New%20York%20Times%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eabout%20her%20choice%20to%20have%20the%20same%20procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20and%20I%20met%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20Highland%20Park%20a%20few%20years%20earlier.%20Our%20kids%20were%20around%20the%20same%20ages%2C%20and%20we%20were%20both%20stay-at-home%20moms%20and%20active%20volunteers%20at%20school.%20We%20also%20had%20a%20family%20history%20of%20breast%20cancer%20in%20common%2C%20but%20her%20mother%2C%20who'd%20been%20diagnosed%20in%20her%2020s%2C%20had%20caught%20it%20early%20and%20survived.%20By%20the%20time%20Stephanie%20told%20me%20about%20her%20upcoming%20mastectomy%2C%20she%20had%20already%20tested%20positive%20for%20the%20BRCA1%20gene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20visit%20Stephanie%20while%20she%20was%20recovering%20at%20home.%20My%20intention%20was%20to%20fulfill%20the%20mitzvah%20(good%20deed)%20of%20Bikur%20Cholim%20(visiting%20the%20sick)%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20a%20reconnaissance%20mission.%20Other%20than%20a%20dental%20implant%2C%20I'd%20never%20had%20surgery%20and%20came%20armed%20with%20a%20million%20questions.%20How%20long%20was%20the%20operation%3F%20Had%20she%20had%20any%20reaction%20to%20the%20anesthesia%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcording-axillary-web-syndrome-after-mastectomy-breast-cancer-surgery-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20she%20in%2C%20and%20where%3F%20Did%20her%20new%20boobs%20look%20natural%3F%20And%20most%20important%20of%20all%2C%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20one%20to%20infinity%2C%20how%20relieved%20did%20she%20feel%20now%20that%20breast%20cancer%20was%20no%20longer%20a%20threat%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knocked%20on%20the%20door%20a