nd%20other%20minerals%20used%20in%20batteries%2C%20solar%20panels%2C%20wind%20turbines%2C%20and%20other%20technology%20are%20well%20documented%2C%20it's%20only%20now%20that%20researchers%20are%20uncovering%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20as%20a%20source%20of%20PFAS%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSlashing%20%5Bcarbon%20dioxide%5D%20emissions%20with%20innovations%20like%20electric%20cars%20is%20critical%2C%20but%20it%20shouldn't%20come%20with%20the%20side%20effect%20of%20increasing%20PFAS%20pollution%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20Guelfo%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20environmental%20engineering%20at%20Texas%20Tech%20University%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20issue%20of%20global%20concern%20because%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20are%20used%20worldwide%2C%20the%20study%20said.%20The%20same%20class%20of%20PFAS%20has%20recently%20been%20detected%20at%20low%20levels%20in%20European%20and%20Chinese%20water%2C%20but%20the%20source%20of%20the%20pollution%20was%20unclear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20specific%20class%20of%20PFAS%20that%20Guelfo's%20team%20found%20is%20called%20bis-perfluoroalkyl%20sulfonimides%2C%20or%20bis-FASIs.%20Scientists%20tested%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20used%20in%20EVs%20and%20consumer%20electronics%20like%20laptops%2C%20and%20found%20bis-FASIs%20at%20various%20concentrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20know%20just%20how%20widespread%20the%20chemicals%20are%20in%20specific%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20because%20there%20isn't%20enough%20research%20yet%2C%20Lee%20Ferguson%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20environmental%20engineering%20at%20Duke%20University%20and%20coauthor%20of%20the%20study%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuelfo%20said%20bis-FASIs%20is%20comparable%20to%20%26quot%3Bolder%20notorious%26quot%3B%20chemicals%20like%20PFOA%2C%20in%20part%20because%20they%20are%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20degrade%20and%20studies%20show%20the%20chemicals%20change%20the%20behavior%20of%20aquatic%20organisms%20at%20low%20concentrations.%20PFOA%20has%20been%20phased%20out%20of%20production%20in%20the%20US%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepa-hazardous-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-limits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinues%20to%20pollute%20drinking%20water%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20the%20first%20%26quot%3Bcradle-to-grave%26quot%3B%20evaluation%20of%20the%20environmental%20impacts%20of%20bis-FASI%20use%20in%20lithium-ion%20batteries.%20The%20effects%20of%20bis-FASIs%20in%20humans%20hasn't%20been%20studied%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20detected%20bis-FASIs%20chemicals%20at%20parts%20per%20billion%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20limits%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepa-hazardous-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-limits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eset%20for%20PFAS%20in%20drinking%20water%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Strategies%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20PFAS%20in%20drinking%20water%20can%20also%20remove%20bis-FASIs%2C%20the%20study%20said%2C%20which%20should%20become%20more%20widely%20adopted%20due%20to%20EPA's%20regulations.%20However%2C%20chemical%20makers%20and%20some%20water%20utilities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fshots-health-news%2F2024%2F06%2F21%2Fnx-s1-5013957%2Fpfas-forever-chemicals-drinking-water-rule-lawsuits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20challenged%20the%20agency%20in%20court.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20routes%20of%20exposure%20to%20bis-FASIs%20exist.%20Air%20emissions%20data%20suggest%20the%20chemicals%20can%20travel%20to%20areas%20far%20from%20manufacturing%20sites.%20They%20can%20also%20leach%20into%20the%20environment%20from%20landfills%2C%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20end%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20said%20only%20about%205%25%20of%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20are%20recycled%2C%20and%20by%202040%2C%20there%20could%20be%20some%208%20million%20tons%20of%20lithium-ion%20battery%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuelfo%20said%20scientists%2C%20engineers%2C%20manufacturers%2C%20and%20policymakers%20need%20to%20develop%20battery%20technology%20and%20recycling%20solutions%20that%20don't%20exacerbate%20PFAS%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20be%20carefully%20evaluating%20these%20chemicals%20that%20are%20being%20used%20in%20sustainable%20energy%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20Guelfo%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20evaluating%20them%20now%20before%20it%20becomes%20a%20more%20widespread%20problem.%20We%20an%20opportunity%20to%20really%20maximize%20the%20idea%20of%20sustainability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20including%203M%2C%20Solvay%2C%20and%20Arkema%20either%20hold%20patents%20for%20bis-FASIs%20or%20advertise%20its%20production%20or%20use%2C%20the%20study%20said.%20Scientists%20focused%20their%20research%20on%20areas%20near%20the%20companies'%20manufacturing%20plants%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20Antwerp%2C%20Belgium%2C%20and%20Salindres%2C%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3M%20has%20manufactured%20PFAS%20for%20decades%20and%20last%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F06%2F22%2Fbusiness%2F3m-settlement-forever-chemicals-lawsuit.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagreed%20to%20a%20%2410%20billion%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20US%20cities%20and%20towns%20over%20their%20claims%20that%20the%20company%20contaminated%20drinking%20water%20with%20forever%20chemicals.%203M%20said%20it%20will%20exit%20all%20PFAS%20manufacturing%20by%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company's%20settlement%20followed%20another%20agreement%20by%20Chemours%2C%20DuPont%20and%20Corteva%20to%20pay%20%241.19%20billion%20to%20help%20resolve%20thousands%20of%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F