20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal's%20Global%20Food%20Forum%20in%20June%2C%20Joe%20Erlinger%2C%20the%20president%20of%20McDonald's%20US%2C%20detailed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-mcplant-us-trial-failed-not-enough-demand-beyond-meat-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20company's%20missteps%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20meatless%20burgers%20and%20salads.%20The%20McPlant%20burger%20fell%20flat%20in%20tests%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Dallas%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20won't%20be%20appearing%20on%20American%20menus%20soon.%20(Vegan%20options%20are%20doing%20better%20for%20the%20brand%20in%20Europe.)%20As%20for%20salads%2C%20McDonald's%20might%20be%20down%20to%20serve%20them%20widely%20at%20some%20point%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fmcdonalds-keeps-salads-bagels-off-menus-for-now-11592494697%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Editching%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-salads-disappeared-from-menu-april-2020-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20only%20if%20consumers%20show%20up%20for%20them%2C%20which%20they%20haven't%20in%20the%20past.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20our%20experience%20has%20proven%20is%20that's%20not%20what%20the%20consumer's%20looking%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Erlinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20state%20the%20obvious%3A%20obviously.%20McDonald's%20%3Cem%3Ewhole%20thing%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20that%20it%20is%20not%20some%20beacon%20of%20health.%20People%20are%20showing%20up%20for%20an%20affordable%2C%20decent%20burger%20accompanied%20by%20some%20(hopefully)%20affordable%2C%20decent%20fries.%20No%20one%20walks%20up%20to%20the%20golden%20arches%20jazzed%20that%20they're%20about%20to%20make%20a%20super%20great%20choice%20for%20their%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20go%20to%20McDonald's%20for%20a%20cheap%2C%20craveable%20quick%20bite%2C%20not%20a%20healthy%2C%20more%20expensive%20item%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Darren%20Tristano%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Foodservice%20Results%2C%20a%20food-industry%20consultancy.%20A%20higher-quality%20alternative%20may%20get%20tossed%20on%20the%20menu%20so%20that%20if%20people%20are%20going%20out%20to%20eat%20in%20a%20group%2C%20there's%20an%20option%20for%20a%20health-conscious%20person%20in%20the%20mix%2C%20preventing%20their%20veto%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20ultimately%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20see%20a%20group%20of%20kids%20going%20there%20and%20buying%20four%20plant-based%20burgers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20McDonald's%20is%20exceptionally%20good%20at%20scaling%20an%20established%20trend%20and%20bringing%20it%20to%20the%20masses%2C%20said%20Danilo%20Gargiulo%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20AB%20Bernstein.%20But%20it's%20not%20really%20a%20trendsetter%20or%20an%20innovative%20company.%20If%20you%20consider%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeyond-meat-healthy-taste-price-impossible-layoffs-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplant-based%20meat%20has%20failed%20to%20take%20off%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20it%20would%20be%20a%20flop%20at%20McDonald's%2C%20too.%20Beyond%20Meat%2C%20which%20partnered%20with%20McDonald's%20on%20the%20McPlant%2C%20earlier%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeyond-meat-price-increases-hikes-vegan-falling-sales-cost-margin-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%20a%20turnaround%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20try%20to%20revive%20its%20brand%2C%20including%20cutting%20at%20least%20%2470%20million%20in%20costs.%20Its%20rival%20Impossible%20Foods%20has%20undertaken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpossible-foods-lays-off-20-plant-based-meat-struggles-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20rounds%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpossible-lays-off-6-in-reorganization-under-ceo-mcguinness-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20with%20salads%20isn't%20that%20they're%20not%20popular%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20places%20to%20get%20them%20that%20aren't%20McDonald's.%20There's%20no%20good%20reason%20to%20get%20your%20roughage%20from%20the%20same%20place%20that%20makes%20the%20Grimace%20Shake%20when%20you%20can%20go%20to%20Sweetgreen%2C%20Cava%2C%20or%20Panera.%20Or%20you%20can%20just%20spin%20something%20up%20from%20ingredients%20you%20got%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20reserving%20your%20McDonald's%20trip%20for%20when%20you're%20in%20the%20mood%20for%20a%20treat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20give%20restaurants%20a%20sort%20of%20permission%20to%20offer%20certain%20items.%20At%20McDonald's%2C%20diners%20are%20on%20board%20with%20breakfast%20sandwiches%20and%20Big%20Macs%3B%20they're%20not%20so%20on%20board%20with%20a%20mediocre%20salad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20will%20only%20give%20you%20credit%20for%20the%20things%20they%20think%20you%20can%20produce%2C%26quot%3B%20Tristano%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20going%20to%20see%20an%20eggs%20Benedict%20at%20McDonald's.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20McDonald's%20has%20been%20able%20to%20fold%20in%20some%20noncore%20items%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20coffee%20and%20chicken.%20But%20that%20makes%20sense.%20Coffee%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2007%2F11%2F19%2Fbusiness%2Fworldbusiness%2F19iht-coffee.1.8387256.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especialty%20coffee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20already%20popular.%20McDonald's%20has%20had%20regular%20drip%20coffee%20available%20for%20decades%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20open%20its%20first%20McCaf%C3%A9%20until%201993%2C%20in%20Australia.%20The%20first%20McCaf%C3%A9%20in%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20080512005130%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.fool.com%2Fnews%2Ffoolplate%2F2001%2Ffoolplate010430.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopened%20in%20Chicago%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcorpmcd%2Four-stories%2Farticle%2F10-things-mcnuggets.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChicken%2520McNuggets%2520were%2520first%2520developed%2Cthe%2520Chicken%2520McNugget%2520was%2520born.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeveloped%20chicken%20nuggets%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%201970s%20and%20added%20them%20to%20the%20menu%20in%201983.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthen-and-now-mcdonalds-menu-items-2020-2%23mcdonalds-debuted-the-mcchicken-in-1980-and-it-was-a-disappointment-at-first-17%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20the%20McChicken%20sandwich%20on%20the%20menu%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201980%2C%20later%20pulled%20it%20because%20of%20poor%20performance%2C%20and%20then%20put%20it%20back%20on%20again%20after%20the%20success%20of%20the%20nuggets.%20Today%2C%20McDonald's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-chicken-sandwiches-nuggets-business-as-big-as-beef-burgers-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20selling%20as%20much%20chicken%20as%20it%20is%20beef%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20if%20not%20more%2C%20doing%20%2425%20billion%20in%20chicken%20sales%20annually.%20Still%2C%20it's%20the%20crispy%20chicken%20and%20the%20nuggets%20that%20are%20going%20gangbusters%2C%20not%20the%20leaner%20grilled%20chicken%2C%20which%20it%20also%20pulled%20from%20menus%20across%20the%20US%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20consumer%20demand%20that's%20keeping%20McDonald's%20menu%20limited%20to%20the%20more-traditional%2C%20less-than-body-boosting%20items%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20its%20franchisees%2C%20too.%20It%20doesn't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20offer%20items%20they%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20selling%2C%20let%20alone%20put%20in%20the%20investment%20to%20make%20them.%20Keeping%20the%20menu%20limited%20helps%20them%20serve%20faster%20and%20keep%20costs%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20landscape%20of%20fast%20food%2C%20McDonald's%20is%20unique%20and%20it%20isn't.%20Tristano%20said%20Wendy's%2C%20for%20example%2C%20hasn't%20had%20much%20success%20in%20expanding%20its%20menu%20beyond%20chili%2C%20which%20it%20can%20use%20its%20leftover%20meat%20to%20create%2C%20though%20it%20does%20have%20salad.%20Gargiulo%20said%20Burger%20King%20had%20done%20a%20little%20better%20on%20some%20fronts%20because%20in%20its%20DNA%20is%20a%20focus%20on%20a%20little%20higher%20quality.%20Its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpossible-whopper-boosts-burger-king-sales-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EImpossible%20Whopper%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20available%20in%20the%20US%2C%20though%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.restaurantdive.com%2Fnews%2Fare-diners-souring-on-plant-based-plant-based-meat-at-restaurants%2F696250%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20of%20its%20other%20vegan%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Impossible%20Croissan'wich%2C%20have%20been%20taken%20off%20the%20menu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20what%20McDonald's%20excels%20at%20is%20their%20ability%20to%20operationally%20make%20things%20efficient.%20And%20even%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20kitchen%2C%20the%20equipment%20and%20how%20it's%20laid%20out%20and%20how%20their%20workers%20are%20optimizing%20the%20space%20as%20well%20as%20the%20time%20that%20they%20are%20using%20everything%20is%2C%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20Toyota%20production%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Gargiulo%20said.%20%26quot%3BBurger%20King%20has%20always%20been%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20irreverent.%20It's%20been%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20the%20smaller%20brother%20attempting%20to%20be%20something%20better%20than%20McDonald's.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20have%20certain%20expectations%20for%20McDonald's%2C%20just%20as%20they%20do%20of%20any%20brand.%20For%20McDonald's%2C%20they'd%20like%20it%20to%20be%20cheap%2C%20they%20want%20it%20to%20taste%20OK%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-are-calling-mcdonalds-5-dollar-meal-deal-skimpy-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20want%20to%20feel%20like%20they're%20getting%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20if%20they're%20worried%20about%20their%20waistlines%2C%20at%20this%20point%20it's%20pretty%20clear%20McDonald's%20is%20not%20the%20place%20to%20go.%20No%20one%20goes%20to%20J.Crew%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20car.%20No%20one%20goes%20to%20the%20Apple%20Store%20looking%20for%20a%20charm%20bracelet.%20And%20no%20one%20goes%20to%20McDonald's%20looking%20for%20greens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-should-stick-to-unhealthy-food-burgers-chicken-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720432683000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668444841aace5b3ada3c532%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-should-stick-to-unhealthy-food-burgers-chicken-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fast%20food%20chain's%20experiment%20with%20salads%20and%20meatless%20burgers%20was%20a%20dumb%20move.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A103%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-should-stick-to-unhealthy-food-burgers-chicken-2024-